>>33ce9fae-1175-4119-aaf3-e81785f80b9b

I was seeing broken pipe errors myself today - still worked.

Recommend you be cautious in changing anything as I suspect your system is fine. ZeroNet in many ways is "too simple to fail", but it depends on the Tor network's complexity to work. If your entry node recently changed to a bad one (as it does every 30-180 days?) - it can lead to all manner of problems similar to your "described".

Only solution is to "trick" your Tor proxy into selecting a different entry node. You do that be restarting with a blocked internet connection then reconnecting 2-3 minutes later. Your Tor proxy will page through the available entry nodes and hopefully bypass the one you are currently using.

Would wager there is NOTHING wrong with your ZeroNet system. It's Tor.

>>33ce9fae-1175-4119-aaf3-e81785f80b9b
">The most relevant is a clearnet proxy portal to allow access to 08 from anywhere. The other is a WAN architecture to allow a clearnet landing site to funnel users to a specific tor hidden service running on a different, concealed machine. This could allow the clearnet site and its server and domain to have full deniability against takedowns and deplatforming (as they host no content, objectionable or otherwise) while also avoiding the tracking and datamining problems that are plentiful with tor open proxies. If both of these work out, then next it should also be possible to clone ZeroID's system to have our own, in-house cert generation too. That's been a long term goal ever since the spam attack."

I don't care to mess with the simple "purity" of ZeroNet networks via proxies because it degrades performance and encourages freeloading. That said, many well meaning people will NEVER have the ability to get a ZeroNet node up and running - then maintain it. Why onion sites might be a better choice for many applications.

ZeroID has been fixed by no fish. Haven't seen any problems there lately.

IMO a better project would involve a truly bulletproof LiveCD which would automatically setup a ZeroNet node, perhaps even with LUKS encryption to a data hard drive. This system would read only - so users could download content. If they wished to post - they would need to learn how to setup their own node.

My reasoning? There are likely > 20,000 memes from donald.win on 08chan now. Many, many people are doing mischief/ would do mischief if they could just access those memes.

Zeronet is just better for this than any proxy.
